{"id":96002884,"author":"chekohler","permlink":"actifit-chekohler-20211129t202543652z","category":"hive-193552","parent_author":"","parent_permlink":"hive-193552","title":"Arsenal looking at David ad the long term solution ","body":"\n![0_GettyImages-1235426339.jpeg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/chekohler/23wCFv3ZoazGVXTheU7fnLrWsszNSzRgkX6u4m8eTkfT3HddEU62nA2uHHUgn6VZ6oJfr.jpeg)\n\nArsenal need to look for a long-term replacement for Auba and Laca as Lacazette looks to be moving on and Auba is not getting any younger.  Once Laca and Nketia leave hopefully in January so we can bring in some money and not let them leave on a free then it will only be Martinelli, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang and Folarin Balogun are set to be the only senior forwards at the club.\n\nOne of the most promising strikers is Lille's David, a club we have a good relationship with having brought Pepe and Gabriel to Arsenal from them in recent years\n\nDavid’s signature will suit our latest recruitment plan of signing promising players under the age of 23. Arsenal’s success rate with signing young players recently has been at a high percentage with Lokonga, White, Ramsdale, Tierney, and Tavares all coming in recent windows. \n\nfollowing the same focus, the Canadian international would fit the bill and his transfer doesn't seem out of our budget. David is rated at £31m which would be another steal for the Gunners in the current market.\n\nAt just 21-years-old, the youngster already has 10 goals in 15 Ligue 1 games this season, which is the highest in a league that boasts the likes of Kylian Mbappe and Lionel Messi.\n\nIf we can bring in a proven young goal scorer to compete with balogan and Martinelli I think we would have a front 3 that can grow together for the next few years and will be one of the most exciting forward lines in the league.\n\n## Have your say\n\nWhat do you good people of HIVE think? \n\nSo have at it my Jessies! If you don't have something to comment, \"I am a Jess